    <h1>Time-Off Benefits</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>Trivium is committed to promoting a healthy work-life balance an=
d encourages employees to take time off to recharge and manage personal res=
ponsibilities. Our time-off policies help employees balance their professio=
nal and personal lives effectively while supporting organizational producti=
vity. Additionally, Trivium provides specific time-off benefits to support =
employees during significant life events or personal circumstances.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2880634882/Earned+Leave+Vacation+Leave=
" data-linked-resource-id=3D"2880634882" data-linked-resource-version=3D"7"=
 data-linked-resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Earned Leave / Vacation Leave</=
strong></a></p>
<p>Earned Leave and Vacation Leave accrue 1.25 days per month for every com=
pleted month of full-time employment, totalling 15 working days per year. T=
his provides employees with paid time off for vacation, annual leave, or be=
ing away from work for personal reasons, as well as time to rest and rechar=
ge.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2880634892/Sick+Leave+Casual+Leave" da=
ta-linked-resource-id=3D"2880634892" data-linked-resource-version=3D"7" dat=
a-linked-resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Sick Leave / Casual Leave</strong><=
/a></p>
<p>It allows employees to take 12 days of necessary time off annually for h=
ealth recovery or personal matters, supporting their well-being and work-li=
fe balance.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2881945608/Maternity+Leave" data-linke=
d-resource-id=3D"2881945608" data-linked-resource-version=3D"3" data-linked=
-resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Maternity Leave </strong></a></p>
<p>Provides mothers with paid time off for childbirth and recovery, support=
s their health, bonds with their newborn, and transitions to parenthood.</p=
>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2883551233/Paternity+Leave" data-linke=
d-resource-id=3D"2883551233" data-linked-resource-version=3D"6" data-linked=
-resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Paternity Leave </strong></a></p>
<p>Male employees receive 5 days of paid leave to bond with their newborns =
and support their spouses during this beautiful moment of their lives.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2883518470/Marriage+Leave" data-linked=
-resource-id=3D"2883518470" data-linked-resource-version=3D"4" data-linked-=
resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Marriage Leave </strong></a></p>
<p>Employees can enjoy a five-day paid break from work to celebrate their w=
edding and embark on this remarkable new chapter filled with memories.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2880765953/Bereavement+Leave" data-lin=
ked-resource-id=3D"2880765953" data-linked-resource-version=3D"11" data-lin=
ked-resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Bereavement Leave</strong></a></p>
<p>Offers employees compassionate time off of 2 working days to grieve and =
manage personal affairs following the loss of a loved one.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2880634902/Medical+Leave" data-linked-=
resource-id=3D"2880634902" data-linked-resource-version=3D"6" data-linked-r=
esource-type=3D"page"><strong>Medical Leave </strong></a></p>
<p>Offers paid time off for employees to focus on recovery from severe illn=
ess or injury, ensuring their well-being and a smooth return to work.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2885484548/Compensatory+Off" data-link=
ed-resource-id=3D"2885484548" data-linked-resource-version=3D"9" data-linke=
d-resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Compensatory Off </strong></a></p>
<p>Offers employees additional time off to recognise extra hours worked, al=
lowing them to recharge and maintain a healthy work-life balance.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2931851265/Leave+of+Absence+Leave+with=
out+Pay" data-linked-resource-id=3D"2931851265" data-linked-resource-versio=
n=3D"3" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Leave of Absence/ Leave =
without Pay</strong></a></p>
<p>Allows employees to take time off for personal needs or circumstances be=
yond available paid leave, supporting work-life balance during significant =
life events.</p>
<p><a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/ISO/pages/2872770561/Holiday+Calendar" data-link=
ed-resource-id=3D"2872770561" data-linked-resource-version=3D"10" data-link=
ed-resource-type=3D"page"><strong>Holiday Calendar </strong></a></p>
<p>A scheduled list of company-recognised holidays, enabling employees to p=
lan personal time and celebrations throughout the year with family and love=
d ones.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Time-OffBenefits-GeneralGuidelines">General Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Time-OffBenefits-LeaveApprovalProcess">Leave Approval Process</h3=
>
<p>All leave requests must be submitted through the company=E2=80=99s Leave=
 Management system and approved by the Reporting Manager or Immediate Super=
visor. Verbal or informal approvals are not accepted.</p>
<p>Planned leave requests should be submitted two weeks days in advance to =
allow sufficient time for team planning.</p>
<p>In unforeseen emergencies, employees should notify their Reporting Manag=
er and HR as soon as possible (preferably at least one hour before the star=
t of the workday).</p>
<p>Certain types of leave, such as extended medical, maternity, and special=
 leave, may require supporting documentation (e.g., a doctor=E2=80=99s note=
, medical certificate, or certificate from a gynaecologist).</p>
<h3 id=3D"Time-OffBenefits-LeaveEncashment">Leave Encashment</h3>
<p>Earned Leave is eligible for encashment under specific circumstances, su=
ch as during the final settlement upon resignation, retirement, or terminat=
ion. Other leave types, including Casual Leave and Special Leave, are not e=
ligible for encashment.</p>
<p></p>
